title: Best Actor
subTitle: A primary school teacher is obsessed with the world of cinema and dreams of becoming an actor one day. However, his blind obsession eventually leads him into a precarious situation.

title: Mohabbath
subTitle: Sajna rejects the love of her college mate, Ameer, as she is already engaged to her cousin Anwar. However, Sajna's marriage with Anwar gets cancelled due to an unexpected turn of events.

title: Varathan
subTitle: After losing his job, Aby and his wife, Priya, move back to the latter's family estate in Kerala. However, things go from bad to worse for the couple as they encounter a new set of challenges.

title: Innanu Aa Kalyanam
subTitle: Best friends Neelima and Aisha, who study in the same college, befriend fellow students Karthik and Kunjumon. Later, Neelima falls in love with Karthik and helps him through Aisha discreetly.

title: Chirikkum Thalika
subTitle: A comprehensive compilation of some of the best rib-tickling comedy scenes from various Malayalam movies featuring renowned actors and actresses.

title: In Ghost House Inn
subTitle: Thomas Kutty buys a haunted bungalow and convinces his friends to stay with him on the first night. The trouble begins when they actually see the ghost of the mistress who was killed 70 years ago.

title: ABCD
subTitle: Avi and Bhasha are two brothers who enjoy a lavish lifestyle and are later tricked by the former's father into living a life in poverty.

title: Neyyattinkara Gopante Aaraattu
subTitle: An affluent man is called upon to hand over his vast plot of land to the government. However, situations take a turn when he brings the influential Neyyattinkara Gopan into the picture.

title: Anand Sreebala
subTitle: Anand, a part-time investigator, embarks on a quest to unravel the mysterious death of a law student. However, his investigation leads him to confront his own demons.

title: Padakkalam
subTitle: Four engineering students battle their professor's supernatural schemes to control the campus, encountering cursed gadgets and bizarre scenarios along the way.

title: Ennum Eppozhum
subTitle: Vineeth, a magazine reporter, lacks the inspiration to work hard. However, his life takes a turn when he is asked to interview a family court lawyer.

title: Ennum Eppozhum
subTitle: Vineeth, a magazine reporter, lacks the inspiration to work hard. However, his life takes a turn when he is asked to interview a family court lawyer.

title: By the People
subTitle: Rajan, a policeman, goes after a powerful criminal but ends up losing his wife and is also left crippled. Soon, he becomes a jailer and recruits four vigilantes to trap the kingpin who ruined his life.

title: Changathipoocha
subTitle: Brothers Sreedharan and Raman are embroiled in a bitter feud over their ancestral property. In a bid to consolidate all the wealth, Raman hires Sivankutty to woo Sreedharan's daughter.

title: Payum Puli
subTitle: Payum Puli

title: Ring Master
subTitle: Prince, a dog trainer, faces an awkward situation when his pet dog Diana acts in a film alongside his former lover, an actress who shares the same name as the dog.

title: Oppam
subTitle: Jayaraman, a liftman and caretaker, relies on his non-visual senses and martial arts expertise to protect a little girl from a vengeful ex-con who is out to settle an old score.

title: Vikrithi
subTitle: After spending two sleepless nights taking care of his sick daughter, a person with hearing and speech disability falls asleep in a metro. A passenger photographs him and shares it online.

title: Happy Husbands
subTitle: The lives of three happily married men are turned upside down by the arrival of a bar singer. They are later reunited during a holiday in Malaysia.

title: Thuruppugulan
subTitle: Menon buys land for his five-star hotel and asks his trusted employee, Sreedharan Unnithan, to take its charge. Years later, Unnithan gets Menon imprisoned in a fake case and Kunjumon helps him.

title: Moonwalk
subTitle: Inspired and captivated by Michael Jackson, a group of small-town boys strive to master breakdancing and mimic his iconic moves.

title: Moonwalk

title: Athisayan
subTitle: Devan, an orphan, drinks an invisibility potion and sets out to rescue Maya, a journalist who is raising him, after she is kidnapped by an influential man.

title: Mizhi Thurakku
subTitle: Savithri's family is attacked, after which she seeks refuge in a man's house. However, she soon experiences the evils of casteism.

title: Four Friends
subTitle: Roy, Amir, Soorya and Gauri are four cancer patients seeking treatment at the same hospital. They become friends and decide to help each other fulfil their dreams.

title: Kerala Varma Pazhassiraja
subTitle: In 1796, Kerala Varma, king of Pazhassi, leaves his kingdom due to the East India Company and seeks refuge in the Wayanad forests. He then uses guerrilla warfare tactics against his enemies.

title: China Town
subTitle: Mathukutty, Zachariah and Binoy, whose fathers were friends twenty years ago, return to Goa in order to reclaim a casino. But they face many challenges when a local goon tries to plot against them.

title: Kantara
subTitle: When greed paves the way for betrayal, scheming and murder, a young tribal reluctantly dons the traditions of his ancestors to seek justice.

title: Marakkar Arabikkadalinte Simham
subTitle: The naval chieftain of the Zamorin of Calicut, Kunjali Marakkar IV, develops a highly-equipped naval defence to fight against the Portuguese invaders in India.

title: Two Countries
subTitle: Ullas schemes to marry Simran, woman with a disability, to avoid repaying a debt, but faces complications when Laya, a wealthy alcoholic, enters his life, turning his plans upside down.

title: Nerariyan CBI
subTitle: Years after a young woman, Mythili, is murdered in a supposedly haunted mansion, Sethurama Iyer, a CBI officer, decides to find the culprit and solve the mystery.
